descript.abstract:
A feature class describing the 2-dimensional spatial location of hierarchical hydrologic unit delineations based on Natural Resource Conservation Service and U.S. Geological Survey approved subbasins within or partially within a Forest Service administrative unit. A watershed is defined as polygons hierarchically representing areas of land (hydrologic units) that are drained by distinct streams or complex river systems.
Also known as a subbasin, the 4th level of drainage delineation of the 1974 Water Resources Council / USGS hierarchy of national hydrologic unit's (HU). This HU is coded with 8-digits. Minimum size is about 700 sq. miles (448,000 acres).Hydrologic unit delineations will meet NRCS and USGS interagency standards.
descript.purpose: To create a California- wide layer of watersheds consistent with the Federal Standards for Delineation of Hydrologic Unit Boundaries; Version 2.0 (August 30,2004)
